1
00:00:06,922 --> 00:00:07,643
I see now.

2
00:00:07,743 --> 00:00:09,703
Your training is what
made this fissure.

3
00:01:54,182 --> 00:01:59,064
But if you don't intend to fight the
dragon, why do you continue to train?

4
00:02:01,405 --> 00:02:04,966
When I first got to this village,
its people were living in fear.

5
00:02:05,847 --> 00:02:07,527
Hard not to with
a dragon nearby.

6
00:02:08,928 --> 00:02:09,848
Now they're all smiles.

7
00:02:11,149 --> 00:02:16,511
They're convinced that as long as I'm around,
their home remains safe from another brutal attack.

8
00:02:18,171 --> 00:02:20,092
Even though I haven't
done a damn thing.

9
00:02:21,342 --> 00:02:25,503
The only reason the Dragon hasn't destroyed
this place is because it hasn't felt like it.

10
00:02:31,504 --> 00:02:33,044
What if it does feel like it?

11
00:02:33,825 --> 00:02:35,805
Will you fight it if
there's no other choice?

12
00:02:36,205 --> 00:02:39,426
I'm not keen on dying,
but that's a minor thing.

13
00:02:40,406 --> 00:02:43,127
I have a title to uphold,
and people to protect.

14
00:02:43,147 --> 00:02:49,688
I'm Stark, the hero of this
village, and it's my job to defend it.

15
00:02:52,708 --> 00:02:56,749
Easy to say that now, but
knowing myself, I'll run away.

16
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:04,232
This scar on my forehead, I
didn't get it taking on a monster.

17
00:03:04,952 --> 00:03:06,853
It's from a fight I
had with my master.

18
00:03:12,054 --> 00:03:13,535
It was the first
time he ever hit me.

19
00:03:16,776 --> 00:03:18,016
He must have been disappointed.

20
00:03:19,777 --> 00:03:20,417
Had to have been.

21
00:03:21,302 --> 00:03:24,444
Throughout our whole relationship,
he never praised me a single time.

22
00:03:32,889 --> 00:03:33,389
What now?

23
00:03:35,491 --> 00:03:36,531
We just met, but...

24
00:03:37,692 --> 00:03:38,813
I don't think you'll run.

25
00:03:41,734 --> 00:03:42,815
You don't know me at all.

26
00:03:43,475 --> 00:03:44,416
You're right about that.

27
00:03:45,236 --> 00:03:47,538
But I have been in
a similar situation.

28
00:03:48,438 --> 00:03:49,279
Alright, let's hear it.

29
00:03:51,298 --> 00:03:58,425
The first time that I fought a monster, I had
trained more than enough, but I was frozen by fear.

30
00:03:58,445 --> 00:04:01,908
I couldn't muster the
courage to fight back.

31
00:04:03,189 --> 00:04:04,430
All I could do was run.

32
00:04:07,853 --> 00:04:09,134
It kept on chasing me.

33
00:04:10,035 --> 00:04:12,738
And for some reason,
Mistress Frieren wouldn't help.

34
00:04:13,718 --> 00:04:15,140
My master was like that too.

35
00:04:15,967 --> 00:04:25,654
When it finally had me cornered, I
steeled my resolve, and instinct took over.

36
00:04:27,316 --> 00:04:29,417
All that I needed to
do was ground myself.

37
00:04:30,958 --> 00:04:32,760
Your training isn't
going to fail you.

38
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:34,101
Mine didn't fail me.

39
00:04:35,722 --> 00:04:40,946
You're a coward hiding beneath a veneer of
bravery, but your resolve to protect the village?

40
00:04:41,507 --> 00:04:43,848
That, at least,
I believe is real.

41
00:04:52,996 --> 00:04:57,977
My resolve...

42
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:02,980
How did it go?

43
00:05:05,150 --> 00:05:06,872
I don't know for sure.

44
00:05:07,743 --> 00:05:09,044
But if I had to guess...

45
00:05:11,525 --> 00:05:13,206
I think it'll turn out alright.

46
00:05:23,773 --> 00:05:24,594
He ran then.

47
00:05:24,894 --> 00:05:25,775
That's a shame.

48
00:05:25,795 --> 00:05:28,056
I had high hopes for the lad.

49
00:05:28,837 --> 00:05:29,938
We're left with no choice.

50
00:05:30,378 --> 00:05:32,400
Prepare yourself
for dragon size tag.

51
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:32,920
Huh?

52
00:05:37,123 --> 00:05:37,644
Frieren.

53
00:05:40,726 --> 00:05:42,547
You only need 30 seconds, right?

54
00:05:44,249 --> 00:05:45,229
You took your time.

55
00:05:45,249 --> 00:05:48,172
I want you to
promise me one thing.

56
00:05:48,892 --> 00:05:52,575
If I die fighting this dragon,
you have to finish it off for me.

57
00:05:54,165 --> 00:05:56,186
All right, I promise.

58
00:05:57,366 --> 00:06:00,747
But why would you sacrifice
so much for the townsfolk?

59
00:06:04,028 --> 00:06:04,248
What?

60
00:06:04,928 --> 00:06:07,649
Just... that's kind
of an odd question.

61
00:06:08,989 --> 00:06:10,650
I've lived here for
three whole years now.

62
00:06:14,231 --> 00:06:14,771
Not long.

63
00:06:15,231 --> 00:06:16,171
Yes, long.

64
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:22,533
Okay, let's get to business.

65
00:06:23,953 --> 00:06:25,174
Your hands are shaking.

66
00:06:25,194 --> 00:06:26,535
I'm scared.

67
00:06:26,595 --> 00:06:27,556
What do you expect?

68
00:06:30,238 --> 00:06:31,219
Something funny to you?

69
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,862
You're exactly like Eisen.

70
00:06:34,963 --> 00:06:35,863
I am?

71
00:06:37,285 --> 00:06:38,686
This is a powerful foe.

72
00:06:40,167 --> 00:06:42,249
But your hands,
they're out of control.

73
00:06:42,649 --> 00:06:43,530
You afraid?

74
00:06:44,751 --> 00:06:45,151
Yes.

75
00:06:46,212 --> 00:06:47,914
Didn't take much
to get that out of you.

76
00:06:49,093 --> 00:06:51,294
Being afraid isn't a bad thing.

77
00:06:53,294 --> 00:06:57,156
Without fear, I wouldn't
have made it this far.

78
00:07:00,997 --> 00:07:05,198
Even the way they
tremble's the same.

79
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:09,860
I get it now.

80
00:07:11,341 --> 00:07:17,803
My master, he was afraid too.

81
00:07:19,660 --> 00:07:22,841
All I have to do is
steel my resolve.

82
00:07:27,463 --> 00:07:28,963
He's entered the dragon's range.

83
00:07:30,564 --> 00:07:31,884
Why isn't it attacking him?

84
00:07:33,385 --> 00:07:34,205
It knows better.

85
00:07:36,006 --> 00:07:41,948
I thought so.

86
00:07:45,849 --> 00:07:47,690
No wonder it left
the village alone.

87
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:50,776
Dragons are smart creatures.

88
00:07:51,857 --> 00:07:55,460
They're not foolish enough to pick
a fight against a powerful opponent.

89
00:07:58,102 --> 00:08:02,986
Eisen didn't hit Stark for being weak
or because he was disappointed in him.

90
00:08:04,248 --> 00:08:06,269
It's much simpler than that.

91
00:08:11,173 --> 00:08:14,736
The two of us parted in anger.

92
00:08:14,756 --> 00:08:15,337
You hit him?

93
00:08:18,578 --> 00:08:20,199
My body moved on its own.

94
00:08:21,339 --> 00:08:23,340
I feel terrible.

95
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,541
I'm forever sorry
for what I did.

96
00:08:27,602 --> 00:08:28,722
I was afraid.

97
00:08:30,263 --> 00:08:32,544
I was afraid of
the boy, Frieren.

98
00:08:35,165 --> 00:08:36,946
I couldn't believe his power.

99
00:08:38,526 --> 00:08:42,188
My apprentice will
become a great warrior.

100
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:18,430
Now!

101
00:09:18,526 --> 00:09:19,527
Let him have it!

102
00:09:23,390 --> 00:09:23,710
Hey!

103
00:09:24,331 --> 00:09:25,371
Shoot it already!

104
00:09:25,992 --> 00:09:27,693
I did exactly what
you told me to!

105
00:09:28,094 --> 00:09:29,315
You expect me to kill it myself?

106
00:09:29,355 --> 00:09:32,177
You can't be serious, old hag!

107
00:09:32,217 --> 00:09:33,318
You're just like my master!

108
00:09:33,518 --> 00:09:34,759
It's already dead.

109
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:35,880
Huh?

110
00:09:37,842 --> 00:09:38,762
Old hag, huh?

111
00:09:40,263 --> 00:09:41,665
He'll live to regret that.

112
00:09:45,781 --> 00:09:48,781
I killed it… on my own?

113
00:09:50,404 --> 00:09:51,565
I didn't need any help.

114
00:09:53,447 --> 00:09:54,748
I beat the dragon.

115
00:09:56,849 --> 00:09:57,350
Good work.

116
00:09:58,851 --> 00:09:59,911
You were exceptional.

117
00:10:00,632 --> 00:10:01,813
That was quite the show.

118
00:10:02,714 --> 00:10:03,354
Well done.

119
00:10:06,536 --> 00:10:08,618
Now this hoard
of treasure is mine!

120
00:10:08,638 --> 00:10:09,238
At last!

121
00:10:09,298 --> 00:10:11,040
We can't take it all with us.

122
00:10:16,771 --> 00:10:18,072
Three items only.

123
00:10:22,594 --> 00:10:24,074
Does this not feel silly to you?

124
00:10:24,975 --> 00:10:26,836
You're really interested
in this old junk?

125
00:10:26,976 --> 00:10:28,556
This junk is treasure.

126
00:10:29,497 --> 00:10:34,179
My master always told me that you
made the hero's adventure a ridiculous one.

127
00:10:35,679 --> 00:10:35,840
Oh?

128
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:37,940
In a good way.

129
00:10:39,181 --> 00:10:41,082
I guess your silliness
made things fun.

130
00:10:46,109 --> 00:10:46,810
Incredible!

131
00:10:47,110 --> 00:10:48,891
You actually made shaved ice!

132
00:10:50,312 --> 00:10:51,773
I told you this
spell was worth it.

133
00:10:52,073 --> 00:10:54,875
I would take on armies to
experience such fluffiness!

134
00:10:55,155 --> 00:10:55,856
Rightly so.

135
00:10:56,516 --> 00:10:57,617
This is ridiculous.

136
00:10:58,218 --> 00:10:59,558
We're wasting our time.

137
00:11:00,319 --> 00:11:01,600
We have time to spare.

138
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,482
Our journey has only
just begun, after all.

139
00:11:05,403 --> 00:11:08,365
The Hero of the South was
said to be our strongest weapon.

140
00:11:08,905 --> 00:11:11,447
The Seven Sages of
Destruction slaughtered him.

141
00:11:12,958 --> 00:11:16,680
The four of us may well
not make it back alive.

142
00:11:18,441 --> 00:11:19,202
So what then?

143
00:11:19,642 --> 00:11:21,723
Want your last journey
to be painful and hard?

144
00:11:25,205 --> 00:11:26,026
That's no fun.

145
00:11:26,706 --> 00:11:30,589
If you ask me about it, I would take
the more lighthearted journey any day.

146
00:11:31,249 --> 00:11:32,750
One I can laugh
about at the end.

147
00:11:36,111 --> 00:11:39,576
Just the warmth of a finger and
it melts almost instantaneously.

148
00:11:39,596 --> 00:11:41,599
Please keep your fingers
away from our food.

149
00:11:41,619 --> 00:11:42,220
Ridiculous.

150
00:11:43,061 --> 00:11:45,605
Oh, and what do we
do about the syrup?

151
00:11:45,645 --> 00:11:47,307
I don't have a spell
to produce that.

152
00:11:47,728 --> 00:11:48,068
Really?

153
00:11:48,869 --> 00:11:50,411
Even more ridiculous.

154
00:12:05,432 --> 00:12:07,353
Well, can you see through them?

155
00:12:08,073 --> 00:12:08,973
Yes, but...

156
00:12:09,934 --> 00:12:12,194
I can't say I find
this spell interesting.

157
00:12:12,454 --> 00:12:14,955
I'm so sorry my body
isn't interesting to you.

158
00:12:14,975 --> 00:12:16,816
Hm?

159
00:12:18,056 --> 00:12:18,236
What?

160
00:12:20,177 --> 00:12:20,737
So small.

161
00:12:20,837 --> 00:12:22,238
No part of me's small!

162
00:12:23,198 --> 00:12:26,239
Well, Stark, where will
your journey lead you next?

163
00:12:27,119 --> 00:12:29,420
I suppose you could make
your way back to Eisen now.

164
00:12:30,401 --> 00:12:32,761
Didn't my master tell
you to take me with you?

165
00:12:33,902 --> 00:12:34,482
Besides...

166
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:39,112
I'd like to have a ridiculous
adventure or two of my own.

167
00:12:51,238 --> 00:12:53,820
There is monster activity
in the Northern Lands.

168
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:57,622
At this time, no one can
pass through the checkpoint.

169
00:12:59,443 --> 00:13:00,904
Well, at what time can we?

170
00:13:01,244 --> 00:13:02,525
It has to open someday.

171
00:13:03,547 --> 00:13:04,027
Does it?

172
00:13:04,747 --> 00:13:07,128
It hasn't since I was
very first posted here.

173
00:13:07,628 --> 00:13:10,589
After all, no people out
means no monsters in.

174
00:13:12,449 --> 00:13:12,990
Pardon me.

175
00:13:14,570 --> 00:13:16,210
The Castellan would
like to see you, sir.

176
00:13:17,351 --> 00:13:18,051
Be right there.

177
00:13:19,611 --> 00:13:21,032
Listen close, adventurers.

178
00:13:22,232 --> 00:13:25,233
You would be wise not to
cause any trouble in this town.

179
00:13:30,769 --> 00:13:32,509
That wasn't a very warm welcome.

180
00:13:33,070 --> 00:13:38,731
He's a good guard, wants to keep his people
safe, and is appropriately harsh on outsiders.

181
00:13:39,571 --> 00:13:42,012
As every proper town guard
ought to be, in my opinion.

182
00:13:45,933 --> 00:13:51,994
Speaking of safety, this city seems to have it in
spades, which is a positive of being stuck here.

183
00:13:53,674 --> 00:13:56,615
This is the perfect time to
slow down and study our craft.

184
00:13:57,035 --> 00:13:59,996
Once we drop off our things,
the magic shops are all mine.

185
00:14:03,925 --> 00:14:04,545
Come now.

186
00:14:05,045 --> 00:14:06,285
The checkpoint is locked tight.

187
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:07,446
We have no other choice.

188
00:14:08,906 --> 00:14:10,266
Run along, you're free to roam.

189
00:14:10,846 --> 00:14:12,247
I'll secure us a
room at the inn.

190
00:14:15,507 --> 00:14:16,727
Wanna get something to eat?

191
00:14:18,488 --> 00:14:19,888
Loud and clear.

192
00:14:21,908 --> 00:14:22,508
Scary.

193
00:14:28,529 --> 00:14:30,550
Rumor is they shut
down the sea routes, too.

194
00:14:31,702 --> 00:14:37,887
The Northern Lands Army says they'll take care of the problem,
but I give it two years until the checkpoint opens up again.

195
00:14:39,228 --> 00:14:40,890
Business is at a standstill.

196
00:14:44,613 --> 00:14:46,014
I haven't had this in forever.

197
00:14:47,015 --> 00:14:48,496
The Jumbo Berry Special.

198
00:14:49,797 --> 00:14:51,739
I was just a kid
when I came here last.

199
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:55,222
I actually had to split it with my
master because I couldn't finish it alone.

200
00:14:56,863 --> 00:14:59,145
But, uh, I feel like
this thing has shrunk.

201
00:15:00,155 --> 00:15:00,715
I would know.

202
00:15:01,415 --> 00:15:02,776
It's the same size as ever.

203
00:15:02,956 --> 00:15:04,056
You've simply grown up.

204
00:15:05,396 --> 00:15:08,877
I suppose age does
change our perception.

205
00:15:10,277 --> 00:15:12,198
Everything seemed
huge when I was a kid.

206
00:15:13,258 --> 00:15:15,818
I used to think my
master's back was so broad.

207
00:15:16,798 --> 00:15:19,039
But even that
started to look small.

208
00:15:20,659 --> 00:15:22,360
Eisen is getting
up there in years.

209
00:15:23,220 --> 00:15:24,940
I hope you're being
a dutiful student.

210
00:15:27,581 --> 00:15:28,881
Duty is what brought me here.

211
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:31,781
You sure the portion's the same?

212
00:15:31,801 --> 00:15:34,642
The passage of time is cruel.

213
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:42,900
You've got no
reason to glare at me.

214
00:15:42,907 --> 00:15:44,188
I bought this with my own money.

215
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:46,109
Pardon me.

216
00:15:46,789 --> 00:15:47,670
One milk, please.

217
00:15:48,190 --> 00:15:48,790
Sure thing.

218
00:15:51,152 --> 00:15:52,613
So... what?

219
00:15:53,433 --> 00:15:54,514
You're clearly mad.

220
00:15:55,294 --> 00:15:56,215
Mr. Stark.

221
00:15:56,795 --> 00:15:58,276
Fine, I guess you can have half.

222
00:15:58,773 --> 00:16:00,093
This isn't about dessert.

223
00:16:01,254 --> 00:16:04,054
What if I told you we're going
to be waiting for a long time?

224
00:16:04,634 --> 00:16:05,555
Two years even.

225
00:16:05,575 --> 00:16:06,435
Huh?

226
00:16:06,955 --> 00:16:07,395
No thanks.

227
00:16:07,575 --> 00:16:09,716
So you and I feel the
same way about it then.

228
00:16:09,736 --> 00:16:10,696
Sure.

229
00:16:11,356 --> 00:16:12,196
What's our deal?

230
00:16:12,556 --> 00:16:13,397
That's a relief.

231
00:16:13,917 --> 00:16:15,777
You're relatively
normal at least.

232
00:16:16,437 --> 00:16:17,378
I'm lost.

233
00:16:17,738 --> 00:16:18,778
Did I do something
to offend you?

234
00:16:21,979 --> 00:16:23,839
So you want to find a
way through the checkpoint.

235
00:16:25,099 --> 00:16:25,340
Sure.

236
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,140
I'll see what I can do.

237
00:16:27,745 --> 00:16:28,985
Thanks, you won't regret it.

238
00:16:30,306 --> 00:16:32,887
What if you just flew us
up and over the city wall?

239
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:36,368
The wall's only one
part of the problem.

240
00:16:36,608 --> 00:16:41,309
There's a powerful barrier all around the border
that extends to the maximum flying height.

241
00:16:41,950 --> 00:16:42,830
That makes sense.

242
00:16:43,550 --> 00:16:45,551
Explains how they keep
the winged monsters out.

243
00:16:46,971 --> 00:16:47,712
Let's ask around.

244
00:16:48,372 --> 00:16:50,092
Our first stop should
be the Merchant's Guild.

245
00:16:50,673 --> 00:16:51,913
They must be trading somewhere.

246
00:17:04,626 --> 00:17:06,567
The trade has been
completely shut down.

247
00:17:06,587 --> 00:17:12,612
If guarded caravans aren't allowed through, things
in the Northern Lands must be quite serious.

248
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:16,495
I'm afraid we may need to
give up until things settle down.

249
00:17:18,196 --> 00:17:18,676
Not yet.

250
00:17:19,637 --> 00:17:22,419
We should ask around the Black
Market and Thieves' Guild first.

251
00:17:23,379 --> 00:17:25,461
Wouldn't that be a bit
dangerous even for us?

252
00:17:25,981 --> 00:17:29,244
Lucky for you, I look tough
enough not to be questioned.

253
00:17:29,644 --> 00:17:30,985
Plus, I bluff like a pro.

254
00:17:32,365 --> 00:17:33,946
You do have a thievish face.

255
00:17:34,186 --> 00:17:34,826
I heard that.

256
00:17:53,712 --> 00:17:54,572
What a waste.

257
00:17:55,933 --> 00:17:57,313
It's no big surprise.

258
00:17:57,773 --> 00:17:59,434
The town's stuck
on the defensive.

259
00:18:00,287 --> 00:18:02,168
If they don't open back
up, we're stuck too.

260
00:18:02,908 --> 00:18:06,891
You know, we could always
pay the guard station a quick visit.

261
00:18:10,173 --> 00:18:10,633
You good?

262
00:18:11,233 --> 00:18:11,593
Yes.

263
00:18:12,594 --> 00:18:15,275
I'm just a little surprised
by your cooperation is all.

264
00:18:15,876 --> 00:18:19,878
You said that you didn't want to
wait, so I'm doing all of us a favor.

265
00:18:20,758 --> 00:18:22,960
You're even more
desperate to leave than I am.

266
00:18:26,101 --> 00:18:28,603
Well, I don't
have a lot of time.

267
00:18:29,834 --> 00:18:31,074
That was awfully vague.

268
00:18:33,435 --> 00:18:33,955
This view.

269
00:18:34,636 --> 00:18:35,336
Nice, isn't it?

270
00:18:36,016 --> 00:18:37,517
You can really
see the north side.

271
00:18:39,017 --> 00:18:41,778
When I was little, my
master brought me up here.

272
00:18:45,779 --> 00:18:49,400
We departed for the northern
lands from this very city.

273
00:18:50,781 --> 00:18:52,481
Tell me all about it, Master.

274
00:18:53,322 --> 00:18:54,222
You want to know?

275
00:18:55,262 --> 00:18:57,403
See that trail over yonder?

276
00:18:58,485 --> 00:19:04,688
He hardly ever spoke about himself, but he happily
relayed every detail of the hero's adventure.

277
00:19:06,349 --> 00:19:12,412
He's been around for a long time, and for whatever
reason, those ten years mattered more than all the rest.

278
00:19:14,673 --> 00:19:16,514
I'll bet the same
is true for Frieren.

279
00:19:18,675 --> 00:19:19,275
I wonder...

280
00:19:21,316 --> 00:19:24,178
He's old now, and can't
travel like that anymore.

281
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:28,935
He sent the two of you to find
me so that I could fill his spot.

282
00:19:30,617 --> 00:19:31,457
Now it's my turn.

283
00:19:32,718 --> 00:19:36,721
I'll go on this adventure and return
with stories just like the ones he told me.

284
00:19:37,722 --> 00:19:40,304
If they happen to be ridiculous,
then that's all the better.

285
00:19:42,606 --> 00:19:45,108
It's the least I can do
to repay my debt to him.

286
00:19:46,909 --> 00:19:50,132
If I take too long to get
back, my master will pass on.

287
00:19:53,743 --> 00:19:54,604
I see.

288
00:19:55,144 --> 00:19:57,667
Then we can't allow
ourselves to get tied up here.

289
00:19:57,687 --> 00:19:59,508
Nope.

290
00:19:59,528 --> 00:20:01,690
But I bet he's still
got plenty of years left.

291
00:20:15,062 --> 00:20:16,122
Mistress Frieren?

292
00:20:17,303 --> 00:20:19,545
Is there a reason you're
creeping around the city?

293
00:20:19,806 --> 00:20:19,986
Shh.

294
00:20:20,666 --> 00:20:21,367
Quiet yourself.

295
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:24,100
They're following me.

296
00:20:28,112 --> 00:20:28,712
Don't stop.

297
00:20:28,992 --> 00:20:31,153
She must be lurking
around here somewhere.

298
00:20:32,174 --> 00:20:32,834
Oh, great.

299
00:20:33,194 --> 00:20:34,294
How'd you rile him up?

300
00:20:34,674 --> 00:20:35,595
I've no clue.

301
00:20:35,935 --> 00:20:38,736
I was happily perusing a
magic shop when suddenly...

302
00:20:42,938 --> 00:20:44,358
I'm so terribly sorry.

303
00:20:44,658 --> 00:20:47,319
Please, Miss Frieren,
forgive my insolence.

304
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,300
Okay.

305
00:20:49,980 --> 00:20:52,701
I have some concerns about
where this seems to be going.

306
00:20:52,721 --> 00:20:57,563
I understand the Captain of
the Guard was quite rude to you.

307
00:20:58,618 --> 00:21:01,359
As the Castellan of
this city, I apologize.

308
00:21:03,219 --> 00:21:04,879
Oh, it's no issue.

309
00:21:05,159 --> 00:21:07,300
He did his guardly
duties well, if you ask me.

310
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:10,480
In any case, I'm not
in an enormous hurry.

311
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:14,001
Am I right to assume that you
do plan to travel north again?

312
00:21:15,561 --> 00:21:21,243
According to our information, the Northern Lands are in
constant battle with the remnants of the Demon King's forces.

313
00:21:21,743 --> 00:21:24,003
You must be concerned
about their situation.

314
00:21:24,563 --> 00:21:27,824
My goodness, a hero
as kind as she is mighty.

315
00:21:28,899 --> 00:21:31,601
The people of the North will
be thrilled to hear of your arrival.

316
00:21:32,442 --> 00:21:35,444
And as for our checkpoint,
pass through as you wish.

317
00:21:48,973 --> 00:21:51,115
I can't believe that's
really all it took.

318
00:21:51,695 --> 00:21:55,038
Shouldn't we have told them who you
were from the moment they turned us away?

319
00:21:56,436 --> 00:21:58,597
I didn't think there was
any point in alerting them.

320
00:21:59,517 --> 00:22:01,057
And I wanted to take my time.

321
00:22:01,937 --> 00:22:02,858
What a commotion.

322
00:22:03,198 --> 00:22:05,098
This kind of thing
just isn't for me.

323
00:22:06,439 --> 00:22:08,179
Who could feel
comfortable like this?

324
00:22:09,819 --> 00:22:11,980
I'm happy I get to
see a proper send-off.

325
00:22:20,522 --> 00:22:23,503
This must have been how it was
when my master left for the North.

326
00:22:36,860 --> 00:22:37,621
That's right.

327
00:22:39,582 --> 00:22:43,605
If only I'd had a little
more time for my research.

328
00:22:43,645 --> 00:22:44,605
You need to move on.

329
00:22:45,186 --> 00:22:48,108
You know we risked life and
limb trying to get out of there, right?

330
00:22:48,508 --> 00:22:48,968
Indeed.

